  "summary": "Malicious code in n8n-nodes-quick-utils (npm)",
  "details": "N8n-nodes-quick-utils@1.0.0 is a trojanized n8n community node package. Its main entry point (index.js) immediately opens a reverse shell to 103[.]27[.]109[.]184:8894, spawning /bin/bash and /bin/sh with stdin/stdout/stderr piped to the remote socket. The declared n8n node (QuickNode.js) is a no-op decoy. The payload executes on require() when n8n loads the package, giving the attacker interactive shell access to the host.",
